properties.name: 2006 Deer Valley NMBS Marathon
properties.description: Posted by TswicegoodRaced the 19 - 29 Marathon race and won. Second national win of the season at my second national race.

properties.name: 2006 High Altitude Classic
properties.description: Posted by Tswicegood3rd race of the NMORS, 2nd that I competed in. Took 3rd in the 19 - 29 Pro/Expert. First was the same semi-pro that beat me in El Paso. The altitude really got to me, started getting dizzy on the third lap.

properties.name: 2006 La Tierra Torture
properties.description: Posted by TswicegoodThe course that owned me this year. La Tierra in Santa Fe was sandy, hot, and chewed me up and spit me out. Bad, bad race. Only race of the year that Damian lapped me.

properties.name: 2006 New Mexico State Championship - Horny Toad Hustle
properties.description: Posted by TswicegoodThe NM State Campionship and stop #9 on the NMORS series. One the race, but didn\'t really put in a hard effort because I wasn\'t racing against anyone.

properties.name: Mount Ord Hill Climb - upper road
properties.description: Posted by TswicegoodThe Mount Ord hill climb is approximately 5.75 miles with over 2700\' of climbing if start at the upper road. The entire climb is an improved gravel road that receives regular use from employees servicing the radio towers. If you follow the road that you turn off on for about 1/4 - 1/2 mile you\'ll reach a corral area that you can park and start your climb at.

properties.name: Parent's house
properties.description: Posted by TswicegoodWas with my parent\'s asleep when the first place hit. I was woken up that morning by "Travis, they\'re flying planes in to buildings. We\'re under attack." I still feel numb just thinking about.
